to the editor re un pleads with taliban not to destroy buddha statues news article march 3 it seems contradictory for major international organizations like the united nations to focus on saving antique statues when afghanistan is facing a major famine and people are dying the outrage is directed at the wrong target preserving historical artifacts is important but ultimately people 's lives must come first the united nations should concentrate on humanitarian aid for people affected by the drought and relief at its refugee camps shannon mok evanston ill march 3 2001

